uiEntry.title: header_bar_title_center
uiEntry.tooltip: You will find all the details you need to manage this province on this panel.

uiEntry.title: tx_title
uiEntry.tooltip: This shows what global factors are increasing, or hindering growth in this province.|| As a province grows, it will be able to support construction of larger castles.

uiEntry.title: total
uiEntry.tooltip: Total growth this turn||This is the amount that your total region wealth will increase next turn.||This number is the result of the negative and positive factors to the left.||Move your cursor over the icons to the left for more information.

uiEntry.title: tx_growth_next_turn
uiEntry.tooltip: This is a prediction of next season's overall growth, calculated using the global factors above.

uiEntry.title: tx_global_food
uiEntry.tooltip: Global food surplus determines how much food is distributed amongst a clan's provinces, which in turn affects their growth.||A negative surplus can result in food shortages in provinces that have a negative food contribution.

uiEntry.title: tx_province_buildings
uiEntry.tooltip: This shows the amount of town growth caused by certain town buildings.

state.title: NewState
state.tooltip: This shows how many ports a province has, which affects the amount of town growth.

uiEntry.title: tx_clan_development
uiEntry.tooltip: Mastery of the arts also contributes to provincial growth.||You can see your clan's progress in this by viewing the Mastery of the Arts panel.

uiEntry.title: tx_tax_rate
uiEntry.tooltip: This is the effect of your global tax rate on this province.||You can change the tax rate on the Finances panel.

state.title: NewState
state.tooltip: This factor includes your clan's diplomatic deals, trade and special bonuses.

uiEntry.title: tx_other
uiEntry.tooltip: This factor includes your clan's diplomatic deals, trade and special bonuses.

uiEntry.title: button_advice
uiEntry.tooltip: Help||This will take you to the in-game encyclopaedia.

uiEntry.title: arrow L
uiEntry.tooltip: Previous province
uiEntry.script:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("region_info"))
function OnMouseLClickUp() parent:LuaCall("PreviousRegion") end

uiEntry.title: arrow R
uiEntry.tooltip: Next province
uiEntry.script:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("region_info"))
function OnMouseLClickUp() parent:LuaCall("NextRegion") end

uiEntry.title: tx_title
uiEntry.tooltip: You must keep an eye on public order to prevent riots and rebellions, particularly if it is a province you have recently captured.||The pips below show what is affecting public order, positively and negatively.||Order can be kept by keeping the population happy or by repressing them with authority!

state.title: neutral
state.tooltip: Neutral||The population are neither unhappy nor completely under your control.||You may wish to take steps to improve your control over them, such as increasing repression.

state.title: unhappy
state.tooltip: Unhappy||The population is unhappy and could easily riot and rebel.||Increase repression in this area to keep things from getting worse.

state.title: happy
state.tooltip: Under control||The population is either happy, or too scared of you to do anything!||Although both will keep order in your province, a happy population will increase town growth.

uiEntry.title: total
uiEntry.tooltip: Total public order||This is based on the positive and negative factors to the right.||The icon to the left shows the public order status for this province.

uiEntry.title: plus
uiEntry.tooltip: The positive effects on your population's public order.||Mouse over the pips to see more details.

uiEntry.title: minus
uiEntry.tooltip: The negative effects on your population's public order.||Mouse over the pips to see more details.

uiEntry.title: tx_title
uiEntry.tooltip: This section shows the factors contributing to this province's wealth.

uiEntry.title: tx_province_wealth
uiEntry.tooltip: The more wealth a province generates, the greater the tax income from it.

uiEntry.title: province_wealth_dy
uiEntry.tooltip: The more wealth a province generates, the greater your clan's tax income.

uiEntry.title: tx_tax_rate
uiEntry.tooltip: High tax rates will generate a greater income from this province, but also make the population less happy.||Tax rates are global, but you can change your tax rate in the Finance panel.

uiEntry.title: dy_tax_percent
uiEntry.script:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("region_info"))
function OnMouseOn() parent:LuaCall("OnMouseOnTaxIncome") end
function OnMouseOff() parent:LuaCall("OnMouseOffTaxIncome") end

uiEntry.title: tx_income
uiEntry.tooltip: This shows the income gained from this province, determined by the global tax rate.

uiEntry.title: treasury_text
uiEntry.tooltip: Total treasury income||The amount that this region contributes to your funds every year.||It is calculated using your region wealth and your total tax rate.||Increase this number by raising taxes or increasing region wealth.

uiEntry.tooltip: Population||This is the current total population of this region.||The section to the left shows the influences on population growth.

uiEntry.title: percentage

uiEntry.title: tx_religion
uiEntry.tooltip: Religion affects a province's public order.||A province that follows the official clan religion will be easier to control.

uiEntry.title: food_title
uiEntry.tooltip: Food is an important factor in local and global growth.||See the factors below for more details.

uiEntry.title: tx_title
uiEntry.tooltip: Food is an important factor in local and global growth.||See the factors below for more details.

uiEntry.title: tx_production_(farms)
uiEntry.tooltip: Local produce is used to feed a province's population.||Any remaining food is added toward the clan's global food surplus.||A negative number will mean the province will have to rely more heavily on the global food surplus.

uiEntry.title: tx_consumption_(castle)
uiEntry.tooltip: The greater the size of the castle, the more food required to sustain its population.

uiEntry.title: tx_province_food_supply
uiEntry.tooltip: This is added to the global food surplus, which helps increase global provincial growth.

uiEntry.title: checkbox
uiEntry.tooltip: Exempting a province from tax may boost your population's happiness.||This is an effective way of dealing with an unruly region, and could stop any riots that have started or may be brewing.
uiEntry.script:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("region_info"))
function OnSelected() --parent:LuaCall("Notify", Component.Messages.StateChange, Component.Call("CurrentState"), Address) end
